.

. man: hombre (1)
. woman: mujer (1)
. men: hombres (2 o +)
. women: mujeres (2 o +)

text:
albums of 2018 : 3⃣⠀
u.s girls - 'in a poem unlimited'⠀
.⠀
release date: february 16th⠀
country: canada/united states⠀
one word summary: deceptive⠀
listen to: pearly gates⠀
.⠀
meg remy's 6th album under her u.s girls moniker is by far the most fully realised, and it's timing in 2018 was impeccable, given that many of the songs on it addressed the abuse of white male power; a subject that of course got catapulted into the mainstream consciousness after the harvey weinstein scandal and the subsequent #metoo movement. but what makes such songs extraordinary here, is the fact that the dark lyrics are coupled to uptempo pop arrangements that recall the likes of kylie, blondie, nate dogg and abba in pretty equal measure. upon first listen, the single 'pearly gates' sounds like a delicious slice of retro g-funk, but listen closer and you'll catch lyrics detailing how st peter will only let women into heaven who are prepared to sleep with him. ⠀
.⠀

text:
the me too movement was silent in senegal. these women are trying to change that

late last year, as #metoo spread from social media feeds in the united states, intensifying into a slew of global hashtags -- #balancetonporc, #yotambien, and #quellavoltache among them -- two women in the senegalese capital of dakar decided to start a movement of their own: #nopiwouma.

translated from wolof into english, it means, "i will not shut up." but it's been difficult getting women to speak out. "nopiwouma was never going to work like me too, because in senegalese culture it's hard for us to even get people to talk about it," senegalese blogger ndambaw kama (nk) thiat, who co-founded the movement with tech entrepreneur olivia codou, told cnn.read more o @cnn

text: salute to ricardo cruz, eic of gq brasil, who is off to new adventures after 8 years piloting the brand. this is one of his four march 2018 covers ( swipe for the other three). it was a special issue dedicated to women with a guest editor - the writer/screenwriter/activist antonia pellegrino. the four cover stars are well-known, well-respected actresses. the idea was sparked by a talk fiona hayes, art director of condé nast international, gave at a gq editors’ conference in paris back in january. hayes took a hard look at the way men’s magazines needed to adjust to the world post harvey weinstein and #metoo.  the cover # reads:’the responsibility belongs to everyone.’ the photography is by cassia tabatini and the art director carolina goulart. this was a major statement then in a macho country like brasil. @pellegrino.antonia @brunalinzmeyer @danielafalcao1 @ricardofrancacruzz @caiapitanga @brunalinzmeyer @leandraleal @taisdeverdade @gqbrasil @cassiatabatinistudio @theartdictator #photography #magazinedesign #magazinecover #gqbrasil

целый день я ждала поздравления от своих лучших друзей,но они не приходили..я ждала еще и ещё 
был уже вечер,когда я поняла,что ждать бесполезно...все просто в очередной раз забыли😢
конечно,это не повод обижаться,но это повод в очередной раз понять,что кроме моей семьи и самых близких друзей никого ближе у меня нет.
все эти люди поздравили меня 3-5 раз за этот день,каждый раз желая кучу хороших пожеланий.

text:
🌟@arielebonte, superwoman et responsable de rtl girls🌟
—
après avoir réalisé son premier stage chez rtl et être passée chez cheek et madame figaro, arièle est rappelée pour lancer rtl girls en 2016.
c’est arièle qui rédige 80% des articles et gère la super ligne éditoriale de rtl girls !
—
arièle peut être fière du travail qu’elle accomplit! elle est particulièrement fière de voir que sa ligne éditoriale féministe se diffuse au sein de tout rtl.fr. «les journalistes deviennent plus sensibles à l’égalité, la diversité, dans la rédaction de leurs articles».
«peut-être qu’un jour, nous n’aurons même plus besoin de rtl girls!»
—
arièle est aussi branchée sorcellerie, et pense depuis un bout de temps à lancer une newsletter. mais elle ne se sentait pas légitime… le syndrome de l’imposteur, vous connaissez?
et puis, son envie grandit, ses copines l’encouragent et… arièle vient tout juste de lancer @spellitout.newsletter que l’on vous conseille vivement! vous pouvez y suivre l’actu sur la sorcellerie et les sorcières 🧙‍♀️🧝‍♀️
—
mais ce n’est pas tout. 
a la suite d’un article qu’elle rédige sur le pouvoir d’émancipation des livres, arièle décide, en plus de gérer rtl girls, de faire du surf, de jouer de la guitare, de voyager et on en passe… de lancer son book club féministe!
—
il y a aujourd’hui 80 membres dans le groupe et certaines se retrouvent une fois par mois pour échanger des bouquins et discuter! si ça vous tente ?
—
d’ailleurs, arièle nous donne ses 3 livres incontournables 📚 
1° «et devant moi le monde», de joyce maynard (son livre préféré, qui aide arièle dans les étapes importantes de sa vie)
—
 2° «king kong théorie», de virginie despentes (intéressant à lire après #metoo, elle avait déjà tout dit avant le mouvement)
—
3° «homo sapienne», de niviaq korneliussen (très actuel, belle histoire qui parle identité de genre)

text:
while #metooindia’s significance and impact cannot be denied, it has so far prioritised the voices of privileged, cisgender women. with the supreme court judgement on section 377 of the ipc already affecting the potential for systemic changes when it comes to sexual harassment and abuse, @shalwrit's piece in our november-december issue takes us through the interstitial spaces in india’s patriarchal structure to understand how the #metoo movement can become more inclusive.

tweet_full:
while #metooindia’s significance and impact cannot be denied, it has so far prioritised the voices of privileged, cisgender women. with the supreme court judgement on section 377 of the ipc already affecting the potential for systemic changes when it comes to sexual harassment and abuse, @shalwrit is piece in our november-december issue takes us through the interstitial spaces in india’s patriarchal structure to understand how the #metoo movement can become more inclusive.

ラーレ・イスタンブール (lale istanbul)は、トルコ製のインテリアやファッションアクセサリーを中心にセレクトしたアイテムをご紹介しております。.
.
＊「ラーレ・イスタンブール」について...
.
ラーレ (lale) とは...
トルコ語で「チューリップ」の意味。(先の尖ったトルコ原産のチューリップはトルコ伝統織物やセラミックのモチーフに愛用者されています。)
.
イスタンブール (istanbul) とは...
「コンスタンティノープル」の別名を有し、東洋と西洋が交差するトルコの古都。
.
ラーレ・イスタンブール 公式ブランドサイト

.

.
ラーレ (lale) とは...
トルコ語で「チューリップ」の意味。(先の尖ったトルコ原産のチューリップはトルコ伝統織物やセラミックのモチーフに愛用者されています。)
.
イスタンブール (istanbul) とは...
「コンスタンティノープル」の別名を有し、東洋と西洋が交差するトルコの古都。
.

text:
📢 big announcement 📢
we like you so much that we want to make this official 😉 we’ve decided advocacy about nonviolent abuse is so important, that we’d like to stick around — permanently!
we began life as a campaign for law reform to criminalise nonviolent abuse. but that’s just one idea among a lot of important ideas, and it’s just one issue among a lot of critical issues.
there’s so many reasons that victim-survivors of nonviolent abuse aren’t getting help and aren’t getting justice. we want to work on them all. 
so, we’ve become the first and only organisation solely representing victim-survivors of nonviolent abuse.
we’re called take it seriously because that’s what we need people to do when it comes to nonviolent abuse.
we love the work that charities, non-profits, service providers, advocacy groups, and peak bodies are doing on family violence and gendered violence.
but no one was specifically representing us. until now!
officially, we’re an unincorporated association registered with the australian charities & non-profits commission. 
why not check out the updated website?
or just let us know if you have any questions!
we can’t wait to get to work on representing all of the ways that victim-survivors of nonviolent abuse can get the justice and support we deserve.
#abuseisviolence #stopabuse #noexcuseforabuse #familyviolence #fv #domesticviolence #dv #violenceagainstwomen #rape #rapesurvivor #sexualassault #sexualassaultsurvivor #abuse #survivor #abusesurvivor #believewomen #believefemmes #believesurvivors #ibelieveher #ibelievethem #wearesurvivors #survivorsareeverywhere #metoo #womenswave

text:
a mochila de boneca angela coelho cinza da metoo tem olhos sonolentos, bochechas rosadas, orelhas de coelhinha e um vestido fofo. além de se tornar uma companhia inseparável da criança que poderá levar seus pertences de forma prática e segura na companhia da sua bonequinha.
é composta por uma alça de mão, duas alças ajustáveis para colocar nas costas e fechamento em zíper.
material resistente em 100% poliéster, com enchimento em fibra de poliéster. tamanho 40x23 cm
 fácil limpeza: lavar com água fria e sabão neutro. não lavar a maquina. não alvejar. não secar na secadora.

text:
every human being on the planet wants to be happy. 
anything that anyone desires is because they think their desire will make them happy. 
whether it is health, money, a loving relationship, material things, accomplishments, a job, or anything at all, the desire for happiness is the bottom line of all of them. 
but remember that happiness is a state inside of us, and something on the outside can only bring fleeting happiness, because material things are impermanent.

text:
- stage amazon training -

le 27 janvier 2019, eric quequet nous fera travailler des techniques pour se défendre dans les transports en commun (bus, metro...). comment repérer des agresseurs potentiels, se défendre dans un espace confiné, défendre une tierce personne, et bien d'autres techniques de défense de rue.

ce stage est réservées aux femmes, de tous niveaux de pratique de self-défense. aucune pratique sportive préalable n'est nécessaire.

tarifs : 30€ adhérentes de l'adac / 40€ extérieurs / 15€ étudiantes (jusqu'à 26 ans avec justificatif)

pour plus d'informations : adacparis@gmail.com #amazontrainingparis #adac #stage #boxederue #transportsencommun #harcelementsexuel #metoo #moncorpsmesreglesdujeu @adacfrance

text:
on december 18th 2018, athena hosted a #metoo adolescent girls and young women town hall in nairobi, kenya. the town hall was an interactive dialogue focused on sexual harassment, safety and survival. the session created an open platform for young women to discuss and explore the roles of gender inequity, religion, cultural norms, poverty and lack of access to education in exacerbating young women’s vulnerability to sexual harassment, violence and exploitation.

young women shared examples of lived experiences and community trends and were invited to unpack and explore what safety looks like in the workplace and beyond. additionally, young women offered practical ideas and solutions to promote gender transformation, safe societies for women and girls and tips to eliminate sexual harassment. “we continue to talk about creating safe spaces here or there like churches or schools or our homes. we need a change that creates a safe world. it shouldn't just be some spaces that are safe" participant “sexual harassment is when a no, no longer means no!” #whatgirlswant leader “when women talk about assault, no one is willing to step forward and support you and take your hand. the law enforcement comes into question. can the law and the judiciary act system actually support women to have rights and control of their sexuality? men dominate so many spaces. men feel that they are in more powerful positions.” #whatgirlswant champion “silence is a driver of sexual harassment.  if you see something do you speak or become mute? do you say it's none of my business when something happens? gang rape has become normalized and accepted in our communities. when you see it happening around you, speak against it, even if it’s only a small act.” positive women voices 
#whatwomenwant #whatgirlswant #metoo

text:
hot news
sonu nigam gegerkan media dengan pernyataannya yang meledak 😯

penyanyi sonu nigam menghadapi waktu yang sangat sulit ketika ia meminta larangan penggunaan pengeras suara di tempat-tempat keagamaan. jumlah ancaman yang terus-menerus dia hadapi semuanya. sekarang, setelah setahun, dia sekali lagi membuat pernyataan yang sangat kontroversial. 
pada pertemuan agenda aaj tak, penyanyi playback ini mengambil penggalian pada pujian yang dinikmati penyanyi dari pakistan di negara india. media melaporkan dari apa yang sonu nigam ungkapkan, “kadang-kadang, saya merasa seolah-olah akan lebih baik jika saya berasal dari pakistan. setidaknya saya akan mendapat tawaran dari india” 
sonu lebih lanjut mengkritik budaya remix di industri musik india, dan berkata, “saat ini, penyanyi harus membayar perusahaan musik untuk pertunjukannya. jika kita tidak mengeluarkan uang, mereka akan memainkan lagu yang dinyanyikan oleh penyanyi lain dan menyorotnya. kemudian, mereka akan mengambil uang dari mereka”. sonu bahkan berbicara tentang bagaimana penyanyi asal pakistan, atif aslam, teman dekatnya atau bahkan rahat fateh ali khan tidak diminta untuk membayar untuk menyanyi di sebuah acara.

lebih lanjut, dia berbicara tentang gelombang #metoo yang telah memukul industri bollywood akhir-akhir ini. sonu nigam berkata, “saya belum punya cukup kesempatan untuk berbicara tentang hal ini. saya sendiri adalah saksi bagaimana kekuasaan disalahgunakan. saya berkata #metoo sepuluh tahun yang lalu, ketika seorang wartawan terus mengganggu saya. dia telah memberi tahu seorang direktur bahwa jika direktur tersebut bekerja dengan saya, maka wartawan tersebut akan bunuh diri". sonu menyesali kurangnya bukti dan menambahkan. 😯

#spotboye
@sonunigammusic
@sonunigamofficial  #sonunigam

text:
a lot has happened since september 25. @iamtanushreeduttaofficial’s brutally truthful television interview about actor #nanapatekar’s sexual misconduct, followed by mahima kukreja’s (@agirlofherwords) outing of comedian #utsavchakraborty as a serial harasser a few weeks later, unleashed a turbo-charged outflowing of similar stories from other working women, and new reports are still trickling in. the rot of toxic masculinity has been exposed, and the corroded spirits of countless survivors lie bare before a population of slack-jawed bystanders…now what?

this is a question that we at verve asked ourselves while curating a thought-provoking collection of articles in our november-december issue, which examines a few important aspects of this ongoing and multidimensional conversation. click on the link in bio for some insightful perspectives from an inspiring group of contributors: @zubaanbooks, @aishwaryaarumbakkam, @shalswrit, #rutujashinde, @taraanandart and @opashona.
illustration: @taraanandart
__

text_retweet:
talking about keeping it real 👏
#repost @girls.girls.girls.magazine ・・・
@clairerothstein magazine founder here 👋🏼 just sharing this image from my account which i think encapsulates @girls.girls.girls.magazine and what we stand for...👠 “a million reasons why i wanted to post this picture. obviously #rachelmcadams looks incredible and was quite literally the dream to work with but also this shoot was about 6 months post her giving birth to her son, so  between shots she was expressing/pumping as still breastfeeding. we had a mutual appreciation disagreement about who’s idea it was to take this picture but i’m still sure it was hers which makes me love her even more. breastfeeding is the most normal thing in the world, like breathing and i can’t for the life of me imagine why or how it is ever frowned upon or scared of. i don’t even think it needs explaining but just wanted to put this out there, as if it even changes one person’s perception of something so natural, so normal, so amazing then that’s great. besides she’s wearing versace and bulgari diamonds and is just fucking major. big shout out to all the girls 💪🏽
#rachelmcadams for @girls.girls.girls.magazine cover shoot 📸 @clairerothstein #pleaseshare 
side note: i did not look anywhere near as fabulous as this when feeding/pumping. and that’s ok too”
.

text_retweet:
feminism is light coming to confront the darkness.
it is a coming of change and a warning to those who are not willing to let this change build a new world.
feminism is art and action, history and future.
feminism is present. a gift built to new heights with the fire of each new generation.
feminism is anger and love, ambition and patience.
feminism is sacrificial and giving. a fulfilment of what is right in a world that asks it to pay a heavy price.
feminism is the man who fights against the worst versions of himself. he takes the time to uplift a woman where once his predecessors pushed her down.
feminism is the man who loves his daughter unconditionally, is the man who protects his sister unquestioningly, and worships his mother eternally.
feminism is the right to choose in a world that gives her opportunities of choice in a society that does not make her pay a heavier price for the choices she makes.
feminism is not the gains of the white woman at the expense of the brown woman’s voice.
feminism is not a t-shirt that celebrates feminism at the cost of a child’s humanity in a sweatshop factory.
feminism is not apologetic. so the statement “i’m sorry” does not apply.
feminism is bold and brash, calm and thoughtful.
feminism is black and brown, powerful and resilient.
feminism is poetry and practicality.
feminism is ancestral and prophetic.
.
words by - aishasaleh @muslimgirl 🙏🏾💜
image reposted from @feminist.yes 👊🏾 .
.

.
.

pre_proc_tweet:
feminism is light coming to confront the darkness.
it is a coming of change and a warning to those who are not willing to let this change build a new world.
feminism is a and action, history and future.
feminism is present. a gift built to new heights with the fire of each new generation.
feminism is anger and love, ambition and patience.
feminism is sacrificial and giving. a fulfilment of what is right in a world that asks it to pay a heavy price.
feminism is the man who fights against the worst versions of himself. he takes the time to uplift a woman where once his predecessors pushed her down.
feminism is the man who loves his daughter unconditionally, is the man who protects his sister unquestioningly, and worships his mother eternally.
feminism is the right to choose in a world that gives her oppounities of choice in a society that does not make her pay a heavier price for the choices she makes.
feminism is not the gains of the white woman at the expense of the brown woman’s voice.
feminism is not a t-shi that celebrates feminism at the cost of a child’s humanity in a sweatshop factory.
feminism is not apologetic. so the statement “i’m sorry” does not apply.
feminism is bold and brash, calm and thoughtful.
feminism is black and brown, powerful and resilient.
feminism is poetry and practicality.
feminism is ancestral and prophetic.
.

text:
some recaps from the november issue of the caravan magazine (@thecaravanmagazine ).
worked with the brilliant samia singh (@samiasingh_art ) who illustrated the opener for nikita saxena's piece on accusations of sexual harassment against news anchor gaurav sawant. the piece sheds light on the gender bias in the  journalism and media, particularly the defense beat, which is what sawant was on. this was part of the caravan's special issue titled 'the reckoning' carrying reports of sexual harassment faced by women in the entertainment, media and arts industry. 
one of the toughest, but also most satisfying issues to work on, primarily to break the legacy of problematic visuals that accompany stories on sexual harassment and abuse. 
#metoo #thecaravanmagazine #printisnotdead #thereckoning #gauravsawant #journalism #editorialillustration #gender

this season may be frantic, (and for women especially!) but metro is here to be your guide through all the presents and parties. we have everything you need to survive the holiday frenzy, from last minute christmas gifts to all the beauty tricks and treatments to start a fresh new year. this is the time to try out all the bold metallic and holographic trends, and we’re here to help you put your best party shoe forward. we’ve also got #kellymisafernandez and #mikaelamartinez on their holiday tips, and filipino-italian model, #ambragutierrez on the #metoo movement. everything you need to wrap up this year and gear up for the next one, is all in this must-have issue!

#metroholidayissue on stands soon! #metrolovessarah

nails @extraordinail

sarah wears @vaniaromoff and @theofficialpandora 
shot on location at @sedahotels"

text:
recognising sexual harassment at the workplace:
harassment occurs in the most unexpected way. it starts with moves that appear to be innocent but ends up in unprofessional and inappropriate behaviour. anything that appears to be sexual, unpleasant and inappropriate, which may or may not be within your tolerance limits, amounts to sexual harassment.

launchbox aims to provide a safe co-working space for not only females but males too as this can happen to anyone. the first step is acknowledging that this can happen and how to deal with it accordingly.

text: “with power comes great responsibility” ... all great superheros experience loss, tragedy, and great injustices. they carry the stories and haunted memories of the super villains they have faced; and know how cruel the world can be. the life of a hero is a calling, and most will not feel they can fulfill it; and some will do all they can to evade it. yet somehow the hero always has the power to get back up in a way that defies what is humanly possible. that hero lives in every person who needs the super human strength to get back up; and in every human holding out their hand to help them. it is heroic to heal and help others change their life 💜. #thankyoustanlee #spiderman #spidermanintothespiderverse #milesmorales #heros #herosjourney #wearthemask #superhero #getbackup #heal #positivevibes #woundedwarriors #ptsd #cptsd #mentalhealth #metoo #traumainformed #traumainformedcare #traumainformedteaching #traumainformedschools

text:
in the whole wave of the #metoo movement, it has become increasingly “trendy” to take a stand for feminism. 
the truth however is that most change is only made at the surface level. the real change can only come when there is a shift in consciousness about our understanding of patriarchy, matriarchy, and the unconscious beliefs on gender so that we can untangle ourselves from the collective ways of behavior that do not serve humanity.

text:
for years, i suffered from deep depression. i’ve been through so much, and i always wondered “why me”. you name it, i’ve been through it, heartbreak, suicidal thoughts, financial downfall, postpartum, death of a parent, death period, situations i thought i would never get out, etc. but today i can say, god put me through those things because he knew that i was strong enough to get through it. not only that, he knew i would use what the devil meant for bad, and i would turn it into something good. 
about 4 years ago, i was ready to give up on life, i had it! i felt like the world was pure evil, until  a stranger changed my life forever. all they did was paid my toll of $1.50, but it was on a day where i just had enough. but that kind gesture which was probably nothing to them meant so much to me. it made me realize there are still kind people out there and that through spreading love we can change the world.

that’s were i founded my up and coming non profit, “the power of a dollar”, it’s not about money but it’s about being kind and spreading love wherever you can. a simple smile or a thank you can change someone’s day or life. you never know what the person next to you is going through but if we are open to being kind and spreading love just imagine how beautiful this world can be.

this year i decided to give back to the homeless in newark, we will be making gift bags filled with essentials. if you are interested in helping out or donating let me know. here’s some donations we have already received, i also wanted to get the kids involved so we talked about why it’s important to be kind and decorated the bags ☺️#giveback #spreadlove #godislove #bekind #fundraiser #donate #changetheworld #bethechange #metoo #thepoad

text:
i love my blonde hair. when i finally got it to the color i wanted, i was ecstatic. i was so happy that before we got married i made nathan agree that unless we were in poverty, that was the one item of discretionary spending i could always have—my salon trips every few months. it’s not about just the vanity, but also about the time i get to spend relaxing and caring for myself. .
i scheduled my appointment with the color and cut consultant tonight and i didn’t actually tell her in advance what i wanted. why? because i was so tired of being “that girl from the news” that i actually was considering getting rid of the hair i loved so much i wanted in it a prenuptial agreement. i wanted to be someone other than me. .
i got mad at myself when i got there. i love my blonde hair—i love it even though the man who hurt me made creepy comments when i colored it that way. i love it even though images of me with it have become synonymous with a letter i wrote that dared call out injustice. .
it’s just my hair, sure. but i love it. and i wanted to give it up to be someone else today, because i’m hurting that much.
.
but, here’s to hurting and living anyway. here’s to being proud of my blonde, loud, unashamed self even when it’s hard. and here’s to a stylist who let me cry for a few minutes in her chair tonight because i really needed a therapist and could only get a hair appointment. 😂😂😂 #metoo #timesup #goodstylist #selfcare #weekfromhell #itsokaytocry #victimsarepeopletoo #thankyou

text:
this year broke my heart, mended it like i never could imagine, and taught me so much about what is important in life. self reflection, your experiences, the people who choose to be in your life, and the environment you choose to put yourself in. those who cannot see that about life, or are just simply not in that place, cannot see the beauty in it. i’m understanding that now and i’m so thankful for every “bad” thing that happened this year. turns out, all of it, was some of the best things that could have happened to me. i feel fearless and so much stronger for it all. 
with that said, i am free!!! turned in my old apartment keys today and i’m on the road to my first real home on my own as an adult. it’s truly an incredible feeling and accomplishment. thank you to everyone who has been by my side this past year and that could see my path, long before i could. i am so lucky to have friends who support their friends fully, and self evaluate! it’s so much nicer (and healthy) to face the demons you have head on, and work on bettering you, in a nourishing and patient way. i kept so much in for so long, and it feels so good to be honest about it and grow from that experience. chapter 30 is a month and some change away...i’m ready for it! and finally being able to speak the truth about my experiences and my journey. you don’t have to be unhappy every day, you don’t have to give up who you are for someone or something. and you don’t have hold onto negativity in your heart for those who disappoint you. my path is clear and i am so happy to have every single one of my “persons” on the journey with me. clarity for the first time in years, is such a beautiful thing. i love you all & i’m excited for this new chapter!!! 💃🏽💃🏽
.
.
.
.

text:
hey, i'm sorry yall for being gone so much lately. it's been a wild ride. here's a small update:
1. i'm going to have gender affirmation surgery on feburary 7th.
2. i'm currently going through a huge shift in therapy, and its extremely overwhelming. we are working hard because we think we found the answer of what's been going on in my life, once i have all my ducks in a row, i will definitely share.
3. tomorrow is my last therapy session for 2 weeks, because my therapists office is closed, this time of the year is awful for me, because so much changes with therapy. many therapy offices close, and i go from 4-5 hours of intense community based therapy, to none. 
4. i'm figuring our health issues, and it's really overwhelming at this time. i'm in the middle of a flare, and its not helping me. i'm dizzy, lightheaded, and nauseous, (but thankfully sucking on menthol cough drops stops my cough drops, and it helps my partner as well) my pots has gotten worse, and i'm thankful my pain as been pretty low, except some excess joint swelling!! 5. i'm starting with a therapist who specialized in dissociative identity disorder, and i'm hoping with collaboration from my current therapist (and the one i'll continue to work with) it will help organize some of that. 
6. i'm becoming more confident being me, and counting down the days until surgery!!! -----
thank you all so much, and i love that you have continued with me down this journey of self discovery!

text:
last year (and previous years) but last year could of took me out. i struggled tremendously with my mind. i may have shared some darker stuff that warranted a few people to reach out but i would never express the whole picture and many never noticed. i was in such a dark place. i made a anonymous instagram to vent. to get stuff out but i was too ashamed to do it as me. so these are post from last year.  i know not many will read all this. but maybe there is just 1 person. that can't tell their story so i'm sharing mine to let you know you're not alone. hang on! 
i often thought of ways i could take myself out.  thinking of my kids of course helped a great deal because i didn't want to pass them the pain,  but i didn't think i was good enough for them anyway... anywho i didn't know if i believed in anything anymore but i do know i seeked god with all i had left, after straying away so far.

the lord is with you when you are with him. if you seek him, he will be found by you, but if you forsake him, he will forsake you. . and i have no immediate story. i still had to fight! and fight! and fall! and fight some more staying faithful and not straying away. still fighting. it's been a long challenging year but i can say i'm ending this year on a much more positive note.  people are hurting out there!! because of someone else's story gave me some strength. i'll add another story to the mix. 
#letstalkaboutit #breakthestigma

text:
recently someone asked me , nirav ! do signature analysis really work ?

does it helps people in education sectors too ?

the person was itself from education sector .

when i says yes , she ask me live case study in education segment which i solved up through signature analysis , a case come from north india city .

a school going teen aged around 12 year old ( say named as vikas - name change for privacy purpose ) was been hesitating to go to school.

they consult to counsellor and after 3-4 session , the counsellor was not able to sort out the reason of child avoiding to go to school.

then parent approach to one senior professional counsellor.

after 2 session counselling with vikas , even senior counsellor does not came up with conclusion.

finally on recommendation they approach me .

when i look upon the handwriting sample , 1st thing i felt reason was fear of studying , but the reason was different  hence i ask parents to give me signature of child.

when i saw the signature of vikas , bang on , i found something fishy.

it show me fear of sexual molestation at sub conscious level.

i reply to the parent of vikas as , does he is scare of any specific person in house or relative or in school , further get to know the school is good at teaching and they teach childrens with extreme care , there is no chance that child is abuse or shout upon by teachers or staff or even by parents.

i keep insisting parents to further inquire as the signature sample show me abusing traits.

hence on my request , parent take vikas to professional counsellor and when further inquire , the result was shocking.

child was scare to go to school because he was been molested at school.

signature analysis is an amazing science which opens up the secrets of human brain.

text:
el día de hoy le dimos media sanción en la cámara de diputados a la llamada ley micaela, un proyecto que impulsamos desde la comisión de familia. 
micaela garcía, la adolescente que le da nombre a esta la ley, fue violada y brutalmente asesinada por sebastián wagner, un hombre que gozaba de libertad anticipada a pesar de tener dos condenas previas por violación, e incluso cuando todos los informes criminológicos aconsejaban que permanezca en prisión. 
el juez que liberó anticipadamente a este violador y femicida, carlos rossi, aún sigue en su cargo. un caso de vergonzosa impunidad. una muerte trágica y evitable en el marco de un sistema judicial que abandona a las víctimas y protege a los victimarios. 
con esta ley buscamos capacitar a todos los funcionarios de los tres poderes del estado, y así evitar que sujetos como rossi sigan exponiendo a la sociedad a horrores como el que sufrió micaela. también hemos presentado proyectos para eliminar atenuantes y agravar las penas en los delitos contra la integridad sexual, y el año pasado se sancionó una modificación a la ley de ejecución penal para terminar con la puerta giratoria. 
no podemos seguir tolerando la violencia.
#leymicaela #niunamenos #metoo #miracomonosponemos

text:
shady
.

see what i really think happened? so when you take a medical leave they *absolutely can't fire you by law*, but when i returned to random house my editor had been fired, and both my imprint and my editor had changed. because meg newman is a klansmen, she likely hated my book, and didn't want to keep me on, which was evidenced by my having to hunt her down and her giving me the cold shoulder until my agent offered to step in. i just let it slide and tried *one more time*, when she just pushed me off to another editor ...a junior editor who *can't* work alone
.

subsequently, together they approved *every single one of my narrative evolutions*, but refused to engage the text beyond the outline i submitted with chunks of writing
.

all they would say is, "sounds so interest! bye!" knowing i had not only requested help but kept saying, "we can discuss this at length!" still nothing
.

then i got hacked and they saw the real out
.

bc they thought all my emails had been erased they returned my *very long memoir* back to me in less then two weeks, without having fact checked (i was given an extra month for both the reference and recipes) saying "it was nothing like the original contract"
.

well... i got my emails back, you bunch of old bitches and they are *legally binding*
.

plus, i don't think they like the fact that hillary clinton is donald trump, bc she's their cover, and also they hated me bc i think the #metoo movement is disorganized as all fuck, so not only did they deliberately discriminate against my disability (if you have a person off medical leave u essentially have to do what they say if it won't cause "undo harm" to the company; me asking them to do their job, which is *reading*, seems reasonable) but also circumstancally? avery books hasn't published one black author in years! and they said the book was *only* rejected bc i spoke about the "draw backs of american health care" ( -- about black people, gays, trans, muslims, etc. so that is at once race, gender, sex and religious discrimination.. all whic had been *approved*) but since they thought my emails were gone, i couldnt retrieve them and they could hold me to my original contract
.

text:
the time i didn’t like my sister...
.
.
this is my sister.  she’s completely different from me and by different i mean we couldn’t be more polar opposite.  she’s incredibly smart, professional, practices law, organized, assertive, and a natural leader.  she takes charge, doesn’t mess around, and gets things done.  she’s also an incredible mom, a very dope sister, and has grown up to be a staple and safe space for our family.  maybe i love her a lot.  but maybe i didn’t always like her.
.
.
i have to admit i didn’t always look at her from that lens.  i use to think she was bossy, uptight, controlling, type-a, too ambitious, etc...you know all the not-so-dope qualities you give a strong woman when you’re looking at her from a patriarchal view.  funny.  these same type of qualities from a man would command respect, admiration, and even praise. yea...i wasn’t always woke to this but i can say now it must’ve been tough for her, especially being the oldest, trying to keep it all together and pick up the pieces in our family while her hooligan of a brother checked in and out cuz he couldn’t get it together.  i can’t imagine what she had to go through to be where she is...but she now has my respect, my admiration, and my praise everyday.  i’m proud to say one of my biggest role models is a woman...and she’s also my sister. 👸🏽🐝💪🏾💜
.
.
also she’d kill me if she knew i posted her or this on social media...so let’s just act like it never happened 😳. no, i’m serious tho 🤐🤫
.
.
✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨

.

text:
i used to think that the only way to connect with other strong women was to find a support group or attend a networking event. neither appealed to me. so i stayed in my comfort zone, and rarely made the effort to meet new people. what i failed to realize at the time is that the internet offers global connectivity from the comfort of your couch. i’ve found amazing, inspiring, and brave women by simply following the hashtag #womensupportingwomen 💕
.
.
i’ve found a selfless girl gang community who fights for the rights of sisters and daughters and mothers and strangers across the globe. just when you lose faith in humanity, the light shines through.💡👭👭
.
.
join your local girl gang. find your tribe. build it. learn from the stories of other strong women. spend your precious time with those who inspire you and empower you. surround yourself with people who operate at a higher vibration... the ones smarter than you, stronger than you, happier than you. learn from them. observe their habits. study their consistencies. 📓
.
.
you are the average of the 5 people you spend the most time with. will you love yourself enough to place a high standard on your time, energy, and attention?
.
.
avoid those who spend your time gossiping. avoid those who are jealous. avoid materialistic topics and people. pay attention to what is influencing you & feeding your brain. do not allow the misery of others to become a parasite that you carry the burden for. you are worthy of more.
.
.
we all have a voice. use whatever platform you have (no matter how big or small) to tell your story and positively improve the lives of others. connect with a community of givers. understand the rich abundance of giving back and believe in that the universe will bring that same goodness back to you. 🌏🌙✨
.
.

text:
tonight was a full circle moment - i am in nyc - i had been wanting to see @gloriatheplay for months now -  i first met @gloriasteinem
 and @rcberkley on the same day while photographing with the fab @capturedevent at @plannedparenthoodwi 80th anniversary.
- when i received the news that rob passed away yesterday - i wanted to honor his memory and called josie to see if she’d be available to attend the show tonight - there was so much love in the #darylroththeatre. i am confident that being a “hope-aholic” is contagious.  rob, i have taken your words to heart, “life is precious; don’t waste a drop!” #gloriatalkingcircle @beawomanonfire photos by @amyboylephoto @rcberkley @capturedevent

text:
tranquilidad es lo que queremos sentir cuando salimos de casa, de la escuela, del trabajo o de una fiesta, que sin importar cómo vistamos o la hora que sea, queremos estar seguras de que llegaremos a casa.
*
seguridad es lo que queremos sentir cuando caminamos por cualquier parte del mundo, sin importar la hora que sea, sin importar nuestra vestimenta.
*
impotencia es lo que sentimos cada vez que alguien ("amigo", conocido o desconocido) nos acosa, nos dice o hace cosas que no queremos escuchar y mucho menos sentir.
*
impotencia es lo que sentimos cuando no sabemos cómo reaccionar ante situaciones como esta.
*
la impotencia es el sentimiento más feo que puede existir.
*
hoy las invito a que alcemos la voz, a que no nos quedemos calladas, a que digamos lo que nos pasa, a denunciar a los que nos hacen daño.
*
hoy, después de año y medio, yo les confieso que fui acosada, no supe qué hacer, no supe a quién ni cómo decirlo, me quedé callada durante un año y medio, hoy lo expreso, y aunque mi voz no suene, al escribir estas palabras mi corazón late muy duro, mi cabeza va a explotar, las lágrimas se deslizan por mi cara y vuelvo a sentir la misma impotencia que sentí en ese momento.
*
no fue la primera, y seguro tampoco será la última vez...
*
hoy nosotras somos las que debemos de hacer todo, y está mal, educar a los hijos de otras personas no es nuestra responsabilidad; sin embargo, es lo que la sociedad nos ha dejado.
*
alcemos la voz, digamos lo que pasa, expresemos todo lo que sentimos, no nos quedemos calladas, porque ahora de nosotras depende que los acosadores no queden impunes ante los actos que realizan o las palabras que dicen, de nosotras depende estar seguras, estar protegidas y llegar a casa cada vez que salgamos.
*
alcemos la voz, digamos las cosas fuerte y claro...
*
la verdad nos hará libres -juan 8:31
*

text:
dear depression: 
does it make you sad when i’m happy? 
does it anger you when i smile? 
does it make you feel frustrated when i silence you? perhaps when i ignore you? 
when i’m happy, you are silenced and i am free, free from your voice continuously telling me, reminding me i’m not good enough, i’m silencing you now. i have a voice, it matters and i’m tired of screaming at my core but it’s muffled and comes out as a smile because of you my dear depression. but you make me a part of who i am, so i guess thank you... in some weird way. i wouldn’t be where i am without you making me face the hardest times in my life. .
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
dear anxiety: 
does it make you nervous when i’m not? 
does it make you worry when i’m happy? 
does it make you wonder if i’m gonna leave you? 
anxiety, does it flatter you when you’re my only feeling, later encompassed with your best friend depression? 
because of you i fight the things i do everyday, from things as little as getting out of bed.. scared the world is going to see me as something so much more minuscule then i am, scared of crossing the street & getting hit by a car... again. but, i’m still not angry at you because i am who i am & i’m stronger then you... because of you. because you taught me fear, you taught me to be scared but i will persevere.. does that make you nervous? .
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

.
.
.

text:
i always say #momlife but truthfully since my son was two years old this is what mom life has been for me. it hasn’t been all crayons and coloring books. what mom has it that easy, right? before he was born i had this fantasy that motherhood was only horrible when it came to throw up and poopy diapers.... i was wrong. you don’t get the textbook on how to be the perfect mother or father. you can’t attend that seminar with all the cheat codes to the perfect road to motherhood.
.
.
.
so this is my motherhood path. constantly in the emergency room or at a doctors office with an occasional break between. i’m exhausted. i’m tired. i’m a mom. over these years i have learned one big lesson to not doubt his strength. life isn’t perfect but we’re alive. we are breathing. even when it’s a struggle to breathe, we are breathing. i’m very grateful for surviving more than i thought we both could. god only gives you what you can handle and here we are handling things. my precious mommas boy!!

text:
mujeres en rojo 💜📷
la revista #thehollywoodreporter presentó su última portada del año, con seis de las actrices más destacadas en el mundo del cine en lo que fue un 2018 lleno de buenas películas.

#glennclose de #thewife, #ladygaga de #astarisborn, #kathrynhahn de #privatelife, #reginaking de #ifbealestreetcouldtalk, #nicolekidman de #destroyer y #boyerased y #rachelweisz de #thefavourite, cuentan como ha cambiado hollywood a raíz de los movimientos #metoo y #timesup

gaga dice que es emocionante ver que los hombres se ponen del lado de las mujeres y que "quieren que hablemos en voz alta y nos quieren escuchar". kidman asegura que gracias a los movimientos antes mencionados, en un futuro habrán más películas dirigidas por mujeres.

close contó un momento de acoso sexual que vivió en una audición con un actor hace varios años. ambos estaban leyendo el libreto cuando el hombre le puso la mano en el muslo. la actriz narra que se congeló y que se preguntaba "¿por qué está haciendo esto?", ya que eso no era parte del libreto. hoy en día entiende que eso fue parte del síndrome de congelación que es una respuesta al trauma del momento.

todas las actrices coinciden en que si bien antes era "normal" que las mujeres sufran de hostigamiento, hoy en día eso ha cambiado completamente y ahora la mujer tiene un poder de escucha y voz que antes no era reconocido. (desliza para ver todas las fotos ➡)
.
.
.
.
.
fotos: miller mobley / thr
.
.
.
.
.
.

love yourself. understand your journey is yours alone. your job is not to please anyone, just like it's nobody's job to make you happy. .
if you are worrying about what another is doing, you are giving them power over your emotions. the power lies within you.

text:
tw: rape, sexual assault
christa hayburn was sexually assaulted by a superior at the police department where she served as a law enforcement officer.

for the next two years she did not report the assault to the department for fear of losing her job. when she experienced an unrelated injury and found out that she could no longer work as a police officer, she finally felt that she could report the assault to the internal affairs department. after turning in a written description of the assault, she was taken to an interrogation room and questioned by two detectives for 6-8 hours. “they whisked me away as soon as they saw that this involved a person in a position of power. that day was very retraumatizing.” christa says the department and the city did not take her report seriously or take measures to ensure that the perpetrator could not sexually assault others. after filing her report, christa faced retaliation from the city. they expressed doubt about christa’s medical reports regarding the injury that prevented her from continuing to serve on the police force, and appointed a private investigator to follow her.
over the next four years, christa fought against city officials to make sure that her report of sexual assault was investigated appropriately and that her injury was taken seriously. she eventually resigned from the department. later, two more women reported being sexually assaulted by the same perpetrator, who had been promoted to deputy inspector.

christa filed a federal retaliation lawsuit against the city, entering an extended legal process. she ultimately decided to discontinue the case for the good of herself and her family. “the day before my deposition i read through my internal affairs report and saw all the transcripts attacking me and attacking my credibility...trying to find flaws in me and my story,” says christa. “i thought to myself—i’m done. how much more can i put myself through? when do i say, ‘enough is enough? that’s when i started a journey of setting boundaries for myself.’”
#25daysofsweaters #metoo
donate to rainn: fundraise.rainn.org/25sweaters

text_retweet:
yes, you read that correctly. 🤬🙄 a specially appointed federal panel of judges has dismissed all 83 ethics complaints brought against justice brett kavanaugh regarding his conduct at his confirmation hearings.

the judges concluded that while the complaints "are serious," there is no existing authority that allows lower court judges to investigate or discipline supreme court justices. the complaints against kavanaugh ranged from allegations that he had misled the senate about some of his activities in the george w. bush white house to his angry, partisan statements in denying charges of sexual assault in high school.
at his contentious confirmation hearings, kavanaugh railed against democrats, accusing them of engaging in a liberal conspiracy, a sort of payback for his onetime role as a prosecutor investigating president bill clinton. ( 📸 and text via @npr )
.
.
.
.
.

text:
feels like a dream. did that really happen or was it all some strange, exhilarating, in the moment/out of body experience? 
this role of vixen in the eight was such an honor to step into, and a huge responsibility. like our gifted director @rycardo1980 has said, at first glance the reindeer monologues might look like a whimsical satire about santa’s talking herd, but inevitably the audience bore witness to something much more powerful - a timely and relevant statement about the times we live in. 
how do we perceive the stories of survivors in the era of the #metoo movement? who do we believe when women come forward against men who abuse their power without fear of consequence? what needs to change so that this sort of thing doesn’t happen anymore? (...and why do we insist on telling children that it’s okay for a mysterious powerful white man to surveil and punitively judge their character while allowing that fictional stranger to break into their home in the middle of the night — because it’s just one night out of the year and he leaves presents?! don’t worry though, i won’t be going around telling anyone’s children the truth about santa 😏) vixen represented each and every woman whose story of abuse and assault has ever been questioned. vixen could have been anita hill or dr. christine blasey ford, and every victim of rape, abuse and sexual harassment made to feel at fault for the wrongdoing against them by the hands of delusional and entitled sex criminals. 
it was a challenging role, one that asked me to leave it all on the stage and hold nothing back. i’m so grateful for the opportunity to have been part of this important, moving and brilliantly crafted production. 
experiences like this instill in me that the pursuit of acting is one that can truly open minds and hearts ... and that vulnerability will always be the greatest source of strength. 
with love, vixen ❤️
.
.
.
#metoo #timesup #theeight #the8 #reindeermonologues #theelite #believesurvivors #storytelling #empathy #actress #ingenue #vixen #actresslife #artist #creativelife #vulnerability #rainn

text: tal y como estaba programado dentro del plan integral de prevención de la violencia contra las mujeres #agendabolivar se trabajó en los términos de referencia para construir la encuesta regional  de violencia basada en género para el estado bolívar lo cual es un hito en este tipo de investigación y vendría a completar los estudios estadísticos que el ateneo ecológico a través de su programa #observatorioguayanesdegenero ha realizado desde el año 2015. de esta manera, luego del trabajo de consultoría con la doctora @irenecasique de #unammx los equipos del ateneo y @unfpa_venezuela decidieron incorporar al equipo de expertos del @ciepv_guayana y @cisorredsoc con el fin de que se construyera el cuestionario, se validara a nivel técnico y se llevara a campo, trabajo que determinará la aplicación a gran escala para el año 2019 #ateneoecologico #ateneoecologico #ateneoecologico #ateneoecologico #ateneoecologicodelorinoco #unfpa #unfpavenezuela #ciepv #cisor #rednaranja #onumujeres #metoo #metoovenezuela

text:
i have been thinking really hard about posting this picture... but life isn’t always pretty and pink. this photo was taken on may 14, 2018, at unc hospital. this photo brings back horrible #memories...
🌸
hospitalized for a week due to extensive psychological and physical damage. placed on a psychological facility with zero communication with the outside world (no cellphone, no wifi and only one visitor, my husband). managing multiple medications, therapies and doctor meetings, every single day. all because of that perpetrator... that one individual that tried to destroy my entire life. however...
🌸
this photo also brings back good memories... i was saved! god saved me! my husband saved me!
🌸
that day was the beginning of a new life. i started the healing and recovery process... both, physically and emotionally. that day, despite the horrible circumstances, i felt peace. i was no longer living in pain and fear, i was finally next to my husband. i was free! i was safe!
🌸
the process continues... but i am happy to be with god, my husband and family. i am happy to be #alive!
🌸
#metoo #sexualassault #survivor #warrior #mentalhealth #mentalillness #ptsd #depression #anxiety #healing #recovery #strength #perseverance #faith #god #savior #selflove #selfcare #battle #lookingforward #believe #motivation #powerful #grateful #blessed #husband #family #phdmind

.
.

text:
fort lauderdale, fla. — former trump campaign adviser roger stone has settled a $100 million lawsuit accusing him of publishing lies on the far-right infowars website.

the wall street journal reports exiled chinese businessman guo wengui sued stone in march, saying stone accused him of being a “turncoat criminal” who violated u.s. election law. stone now says his conduct was “irresponsible.” guo has criticized high-level corruption in china and applied for asylum in the u.s.

the settlement reached monday identifies chinese-american media tycoon bruno wu and a former trump staffer as the sources of false information.

the settlement allows stone to avoid paying any damages if he publishes national newspaper ads apologizing for the statements and retracts the statements online. he still is of interest to investigators probing russian interference in the 2016 election.

in this house we take a lot a lot a lot of selfies. we take selfies of us in places that represent things that might not mean a lot to other people but that mean the world to us and here’s why...•
•
in this house we do hard things. sometimes multiple times a day. we challenge each other to do more, say more, be more and show up when it would be a lot easier to hide or just stay in.•
•
today we visited the doctor and after three full months of a new dose of the anxiety meds the three of us together, but mostly joel, determined this was the best dose yet. 
he feels strong. 
he feels in control. 
he feels capable. 
he feels safe. 
he feels listened to. 
he feels heard. 
he feels. 
and that in itself is an absolute gift and 100% selfie worthy in my book.•
•
i will encourage and take selfies in this family for-ever. i want my kids to roll their eyes but always know that every documentation of a milestone doesn’t end when they are independent. i want them to celebrate the small and huge things forever. i want them to know that life is hard and beautiful with everything in between and that while i was around i was by their side to cheer them on and document their strength so that next time they remember last time and know they are capable.•
•
take the selfies. 
document all the things. 
we do this life only one time that we know of. 
share the everything out of it.

text:
👉 desliza la imagen 👈
.

con la ayuda de tbwa \ helsinki, el periódico nórdico helsingin sanomat le dio un significado nuevo al "feo" en el "feo suéter de navidad". “la verdad puede ser fea, pero nunca pasa de moda”. no debemos hacer la vista gorda ante la fea verdad, es por eso que el periódico ha creado una colección limitada de suéteres con temática navideña que representan las noticias más feas del año, donde plasman en su bordado imágenes relativas al cambio climático, la guerra, el plástico en nuestros océanos, la manipulación tecnológica y el acoso sexual. al mantener estos temas en el ojo público, esperan acercar más a las personas para resolverlo.
. 
el jefe de redacción del periódico explica así la campaña: “la verdad es la piedra angular del periodismo, sin importar lo fea que sea. no podemos rehuir los temas que son difíciles de tratar. es nuestra responsabilidad traer estos asuntos a la conciencia pública y mantenerlos allí hasta que se resuelvan”. el objetivo de esta campaña es sensibilizar sobre algunos de los problemas a los que se enfrenta nuestra sociedad actual a través de un elemento tan identificable como los suéteres o jerséis navideños.
.
esta campaña podrá visualizarse a través de youtube.
.

cada suéter fue enviado por correo a celebridades e infuencers muy involucrados en algunos de estos temas, que luchan para resolver estos problemas. arnold schwarzengger y leonardo dicaprio fueron agasajados, por ejemplo, con sendos suéteres relacionados con el cambio climático. martti ahtissari, malala youszafai y nadia murad (ganadores los tres del premio nobel de la paz) recibieron suéteres con la guerra como eje temático. y a tarana burke y alyssa milano, abanderadas del movimiento #metoo, helsingin sanomat les hizo llegar prendas con el acoso sexual como telón de fondo.  cada uno de los suéteres fue confeccionado por la rotativa y se confeccionó al 100% con lana producida localmente en la ciudad de lieto, finlandia. con la ayuda de tbwa \ helsinki, el periódico nórdico le dio un significado nuevo al "feo" en el "feo suéter de navidad". reseña: www.frogx3.com
.
.
#helsinginsanomat #periódico #campañadesensibilización #suéter #jerséis

text:
dang. i just read an article that says the average american home now contains 300,000 items.😬
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
my first thought was, "not me, not our house, no way!"🤭
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
but then i began to look around just the room i was in... i have 30 items on my desk alone (5 candles!!). holy sweet potatoes. i'm shocked. i never thought of it! plus, we have a basement full of more crap!🗑
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i went on to read clutter is a contributing factor to the stress level in our lives which is causing all sorts of health problems. it's so much more than a visual nuisance - it impacts health and wellbeing of us and our families - and even our children in a cluttered classroom.📚👨🏼‍🏫👩🏽‍🏫
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i'm committed to cleaning out one drawer/closet shelf/or cupboard a day for 30 days. i'm up to 7 clean drawers now and one clean closet and lots of goodies for the dump and goodwill!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i do feel better already. how did i not know the stress it was causing me?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
what's your favorite de-cluttering advice?? i can't wait for more tips!❤️

text:
en el último tiempo han ido saliendo a la luz cada vez más historias de violencia sexual. muchas de ellas ocurridas hace años, lo que lleva a algunas personas a preguntar ¿por qué no habló antes? e incluso a comentarios del tipo “es que ahora es una moda”. no es que sea una moda sino que al escuchar como otras abren sus relatos es posible que quienes han guardado sus vivencias por años se atrevan a hablar. también puede suceder que los recuerdos reprimidos afloren o, que lo que fue en su momento normalizado y minimizado sea dimensionado como el abuso que fue.

en el contexto chileno actual donde la sexualidad aun es tabú, no es un tema del que se hable fácilmente y además quienes han ejercido violencia sexual lo más frecuente es que sean personas cercanas como familiares, vínculos laborales, profesores, pareja o amistades.  a esto se suma que muchas veces son personas que no ejercen violencia evidente de otro tipo, son considerados “buenos profesionales” y/o “buenas personas” y el entorno suele no creer los testimonios de las víctimas.

si quieres leer el resto de este artículo puedes encontrarlo en www.etsex.cl en la sección artículos. *la foto que acompaña este artículo soy yo viajando sola por méxico el 2016. es un atardecer en mazunte, en la costa del pacífico. elegí ponerla porque es relevante para mí el haber viajado sola a pesar de todo el miedo que nos inculcan a lo que nos pueda pasar. en ese viaje no me sucedió nada, quizás tuve suerte, porque es un país peligroso para las mujeres. sin embargo la mayoría de la violencia sexual que he sufrido no ha sido en viajes ni en lugares “peligrosos”, son sucesos que han ocurrido en lugares en teoría “seguros” y habituales. y no es que sea una excepción ya que las estadísticas  confirman que  los violentadores, salvo el acoso callejero, no suelen ser extraños sino con quienes nos relacionamos y tenemos vínculos familiares, de amistad, laborales, académicos e incluso de pareja. #sexualidad #sexología #sexóloga #violenciasexual #metoo #amitambién #cuéntalo #acososexual #abusosexual

text: après 3 ans d’absence, florence foresti n’a rien perdu de sa verve. elle était grandiose hier soir au paradis latin ! exécution et interprétation au millimètre de ce « seule en scène » écrit au scalpel et débité à la mitraillette. ça défouraille sec sur nos travers et ceux de l’époque : les portables, les réseaux sociaux, le « moi » augmenté d’instagram, #metoo, l’assignation des sexes, la (non) parité homme/femme, l’hygiénisme ambiant, les émoticônes, les virées chez ikea, la mort ... tout y passe, même le transit de nos amis américains. une bombe ... à fragmentation. bonheur de la retrouver ! 👏🏻👏🏻👏🏻#mercimercimerci  @madameforesti @emmanuellechanlat #epilogue #zenithparis #onestloindelepilogue

text:
tristes y escandalosas noticias del asesinato de otra mujer en este país de nula voluntad política, injusticia social y violencia de género insoportable, me siento como se sienten las mujeres de mi vida, compañera, hija, tías, amigas, primas, conocidas, pienso en mi madre y mis abuelas y como se sentirían si estuvieran presentes, siento indignación, asco, incrédulo y hastiado con las acciones de la judicatura y la política.
siento sus temores, siempre justificados por el terror que padecen, el horror que viven a diario en un país en el que deberían sentirse libres y respetadas.
pensando en las libertades de las mujeres de mi vida, subo a este post, esta fotografía que para mí, evoca la belleza de la libertad de una manera lúdica e individual, representada en la figura de una de ellas, mi hija.
la realicé con una mezcla de alegría, celebración y asombro, mi niñita de tres años se había posicionado sola y libre en la orilla, atenta al hermoso vaivén azul mediterráneo, sus cálidas y transparentes aguas bañaban sus pequeñas piernas.
admiré momentáneamente a través del visor, su postura paciente ante la inmensidad marina y su impaciente espíritu infantil, libre y juguetón.
plantada con sus manguitos flotantes y su diminuta tabla de body surf, dispuesta a disfrutar de sus juegos acuáticos en total libertad y armonía. 
decidida a dominar ella sola a las olas, una por una.
hoy, esta imagen es mi homenaje a todas las mujeres de este mundo, a las que se han ido, a las que están y a las que serán el futuro.
mi canción gráfica de amor y respeto absoluto a lo que representan, reivindico a través de estos píxeles sus derechos y libertades.
insto a los que sabemos el significado de la palabra hombre, a actuar en consecuencia, a respetarlas y admirarlas, a demostrarles la solidaridad y la empatía que todas merecen.
los verdaderos hombres las respetan y aman sin dañarlas, luchando junto a ellas para erradicar el terrorismo asesino y abominable que sufren a diario.

text:
did you know that it is not necessary to have total amnesia for the actions of alter personalities in dissociative identity disorder?

the main types of amnesia in did are:

1) gaps in memory of significant life events (e.g., periods of childhood or adolescence; the death of a grandparent, getting married, giving birth); 2) lapses in dependable memory (e.g., of what happened today, of well-leamed skills such as how to do their job, use a computer, read, drive); and

3) discovery of evidence of their everyday actions and tasks that they don’t recollect doing (e.g., finding unexplained objects in their shopping bags or their possessions; finding perplexing writings or drawings that they must have created; discovering injuries; “coming to” in the midst of doing something). #youwillbearwitness #emdr #erinfado #ptsd #peterfox #ptsdsurvivor #ptsdrecovery #ptsdawareness #stopracism #stopbullying #stopchildabuse #metoo #therapydog #dissociativeidentitydisorder #doitfordolly #trauma

text: i’m a feminist, i’ve always been, since i started noticing how our world is flooded with crap that discriminates women. that was a long time ago, and is still happening...everywhere, at school, at bars, festivals, when you go to college, on tv,...some things might have mutated (not really changed) but they are still there. instead of a comedian laughing at how women are beaten at home, now we have denigrating programs like ‘the housewives of xxx’ where stereotypes of women (created by men) insult each other and fight over their machos...or we constantly listen to singers who talk about ‘their women’ as if they were sexual toys...and this is the top of the iceberg...the number of women who are sexually assaulted a year is scary, the number of women who are psychologically, physically or sexually abused a year is scary, the number of women whose genitalia is mutilated a year is scary, the number of women who are killed by their partners a year is scary...and the list goes on and on and on...really? so yes, i’m a feminist. we all should be feminists because obviously (and sadly) there are lots of things that need to be changed still to live in a world where there is gender equality and women are not discriminated against. #noalaviolenciamachista #stopviolenceagainstwomen #yotambien #metoo #timeisup #genderequality

text:
anxiety can occur when a person fears that something bad is going to happen. it is a non-medical term that refers to a feeling of fear or worry that often relates to a particular issue or concern.

anxiety has been linked to stress. as well as feelings of fear and worry, it often involves physical symptoms, such as muscle tension.

it is different from a panic attack, which is a symptom of panic disorder. anxiety often relates to a specific event or situation, although this is not always the case.

a panic attack, meanwhile, can happen without any specifiable trigger, and the symptoms are far more severe than the symptoms of anxiety.

however, if levels of stress and anxiety continue for a long time, further problems may develop. https://youwillbearwitness.com/2018/12/17/how-to-recognize-an-anxiety-attack/ #youwillbearwitness #emdr #erinfado #ptsd #peterfox #ptsdsurvivor #ptsdrecovery #ptsdawareness #stopracism #stopbullying #stopchildabuse #metoo #therapydog #trauma #doitfordolly

text:
all the rage by courtney summers
genre - fiction, ya 
style - intense, we move between moments with romy sharing her pain, set a year after her rape by the sherriff’s son and her struggle to be believed and find justice for her and a second girl

low point - the micro-aggression that fills the narrative - from adults who should know enter as well - is just as damaging as the act that began it all and is relentless - not an easy read 
take away - turning inward and away from others does not bring relief - all the rage - get angry! @summerscourtney

text:
❤️no es temor, no es vergüenza, ni debilidad, ni vulnerabilidad, la cuál tenemos la suerte de saber cómo se siente y entender que es el más valiente de los valores humanos y un privilegio poseerla; no es pena, no es miedo, no es llanto, aunque sea inevitable el llorar a valientes, inocentes, una vez más. es cansancio, mucho, de tener que justificar detalladamente la igualdad como seres humanos. es ruego por la unión para la lucha por una educación igualitaria, que nos iguale, por una justicia que cumpla lo que define, por una legislatura con sentido, por nuestra libertad, por la que estamos hasta el mismísimo género de tener que explicar y defender, porque debería de ser lógica para todo ser humano. no es ‘hoy somos laura’, es: ayer, hoy y mañana, hemos sido, somos y seremos, todas, ellas, y representaremos en su nombre y rostro, en el nuestro, la unión a la que ellas hubieran pertenecido. porque se lo debemos. porque ellas somos todas, y todas somos una. y si queremos correr, corremos. y si queremos salir, salimos. y si queremos beber, bebemos. y lo que queramos vestir, lo vestimos. y por donde queramos pasar, pasamos. porque nosotras no somos el problema. ¡eso, es! 🙌🏾
📸 @jamesreesephotography

text:
being a victim of rape/sexual assault one of the things that i've dealt with is the desire to feel sensual but not feeling safe to be seen in that way. it's caused a lot of issues in my everyday life that takes a lot of work to overcome.
society teaches us that if we are covered up we won't be attractive or bring attention to ourselves and that'll protect us. that if they don't see it they won't desire it. 
in fact one of the first questions i was asked after the first assault was "what did you have on?" and "didn't you fight back?" for years i covered myself in an effort to protect myself and it still happened again. 
then i realized it wasn't me! it's never been my fault. and well, i'm sick of society conditioning us to feel this way and making victims feel like we asked for it. 
the truth is some people are scum and scummy people do scummy shit. nobody asks to be assaulted and no one deserves it. and for all the "strong" people that think it's as easy as fighting back you've obviously never come face to face with a crazy man thats twice as strong as you are.
 for all my survivors, i admire you, i hear you and i love you. i pray that you find love and comfort in knowing you are not alone and it has never been your fault. i pray one day you are able to peel the layers off and uncover yourself.
i pray that one day we all know pleasure is our birthright. 
you are beautiful.
you are safe to be seen. 
you are worthy. 
i love you 💙💚
#metoo #worthy #mystory #stay #thriving #awareness #rapeculture

text: i know in most african communities, our voices are often shut down or off. hence why our creative minds deteriorate as we get older. lack of communication in african communities is vast, that when something foul like sexual assault happens, we don’t know who or where to run to in african communities. when we figure out who to run to, they also ridicule and emphasize that the blame on us who are the victims of the crime. hence why i’ve created this space because no more will you be ridiculed for something you couldn’t control. #ug2too #metoo

text:
a decoração deste final de semana foi pensada com carinho para as gêmeas laura & joana para o seu primeiro aniversário one 
é uma história que começou em 2010 quando fizemos a decoração de casamento da mamãe das gêmeas, a nossa noiva barbie cristiane rodrigues rsrsrs 
a noiva princesa, que teve  casamento de princesa e agora tem as duas princesinhas, mas são princesas modernas e antenadas nas tendências. 
e assim como em seu casamento no qual inovamos na decoração 
a mamãe cris quis também inovar para o primeiro aniversário de suas gêmeas. 
me pediu ainda em agosto o tema das bonecas metoo onde ainda não haviam, como ainda não tem, muitas decorações totalmente neste tema. 
aceitamos o desafio já que não possuímos muitas referências a não ser mesmo as bonecas e o estilo, no qual escolhemos trabalhar um estilo de “decoração escandinava romântica” já que são 2 meninas sendo seu primeiro aniversário - one. 
e assim foi feito 
uma decor suave, onde escolhemos uma paleta de cor candy color, priorizando o rosa e o amarelo devido as roupas das duas bonecas do quarto das meninas, e em
segundo plano as outras cores como verde turquesa, azul, cinza, lilás e detalhes dourados. 
muitos cílios, estrelas, nuvens, e o mais importante de tudo quando executamos algo...muito amor 💕 
esperamos ter correspondido ao carinho de nossa ex-noiva agora mamãe cris

•
i invite you to stand with me & fight again sex slavery by donating to help us send out a rescue mission to set current slaves free.
•
donate in profile link 💕

text:
laura no pudo decir "salgo del cuento". ayer conocimos la triste noticia que a ella le ocurrió algo que ya nos habían contado en una historia infantil, pero a laura nadie la pudo salvar.
dejemos de ser cómplices del machismo, dejemos de minimizar las violencias hacia las mujeres y preguntémonos cómo son los caminos, las calles, la educación y cómo está diseñada la sociedad para que sigan existiendo espacios inseguros. 
cada vez más mujeres están tomando consciencia de las violencias machistas, se sienten más empoderadas para decir "no es no". laura era una de ellas. 
pero los peligros siguen existiendo y no dejarán de existir si no empezamos a tomarnos en serio otra educación hacia los hombres. empecemos ya a cambiar el cuento, sobretodo el de la vida real.  #feminicidio #niunamenos #laurasomostodas #vivasnosqueremos #violenciamachista #cambiaelcuento .
.
.
.
.#feminismo #mujeres #machismo #machismomata #dalelavuelta #women #instawomen #escúchametambién #metoo #timesup #niunamenos #notonemore #meniegoa #noesno #niunamas #violenciamasclista #violenciadegénero #violenciadegènere

text:
when i was in college i used to go home every night and fantasize about all the different ways i could kill myself.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
::⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i was in so much emotional pain but no one ever knew it. i was on the honor roll, i had a job, friends and a boyfriend. i was outgoing an ambitious. what did i have to complain about? i wasn’t hungry i  wasn’t homeless.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
::⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i tried to convince myself that it was all in my head, that i was making too big a deal of everything. i thought i was weak because i couldn’t get over being raped at 17. i was drowning in shame because i believed it was my fault and i couldn’t bear to tell anyone. so for me the only logical resolution was to die.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
::⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
when i look at this picture i am so happy that i made the decision to start my healing journey instead of the other option. it would’ve been a waste to miss out on all that i have to offer this world.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
::⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
my life is a pure testimony and i’m on a mission to help black women get this healing werk so they can know their true value and bring all their gifts and joy to a world that’s starving for what they have to offer.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
::⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
if you are hurting if you want to find out how to heal and be whole again shoot me a dm so we can start the healing process. if you don’t reach out to me reach out to someone who can help you. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
::⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
don’t wait another day or another hour or another second. your life and what you came to do is too important for you to put it off anymore. # healinggoals #healblackwomen

today i am beginning a 24 day challenge devoting 30 minutes to self care every day through the holidays and new year. 
if you want to join me, click the link above in my bio.

text:
"all falls down" by #kanyewest and #syleenajohnson
.
listen, i know he's not a very well liked dude at the moment. he's said some dumb stuff. but goddamn if i don't love his music. the question becomes at what point do we separate the art from the artist? which given everything that has happened this year with the metoo movement (which is a good thing), more and more of my favorite artists in movies and music have this shadow over them. kevin spacey was one of my favorite actors but now i have a hard time watching any of his work knowing he was a bad person. harvey weinstein is a disgusting monster, but he produced, hell discovered and created, some of the greatest movies ever made.
so do we have to ignore these great works because the men who made them were awful people? i don't know.
.

listen, i know he's not a very well liked dude at the moment. he's said some dumb stuff. but goddamn if i do not love his music. the question becomes at what point do we separate the a from the aist? which given everything that has happened this year with the metoo movement (which is a good thing), more and more of my favorite aists in movies and music have this shadow over them. kevin spacey was one of my favorite actors but now i have a hard time watching any of his work knowing he was a bad person. harvey weinstein is a disgusting monster, but he produced, hell discovered and created, some of the greatest movies ever made.
so do we have to ignore these great works because the men who made them were awful people? i do not know.
.

✨
showing up graciously and appropriately, this loving family man has revealed what it means to work within the realms of appreciation and mutual respect. he speaks always with kindness, is open to the opposing opinions of others, and is the embodiment of goodness. .
✨
when the #metoo movement hit, instead of focusing on hurt, i sat down to write a letter of thanks to this man for behaving quite the opposite in our time together. signed sealed and delivered, here we are making magic through meditation over a year later. .
✨
this, ladies and gentleman, is what it looks like to embody the change one seeks to see in the world around them. .
✨
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
diversity and inclusion isn’t just an issue for large-scale corporate organisations or for those who can afford to employ a diversity manager. it is a mindset and underpins the culture of your organisation, no matter the size.
indeed, linkedin’s global recruiting trends 2018 report highlighted diversity as “the biggest game-changer and most embraced trend” for the year with 78% of those surveyed identifying it as “very/extremely important” to shaping their organisation. and with widespread gains to be made from a diverse and inclusive workforce, surely this should be the case for every organisation.
nonetheless, despite the benefits, the evolution of workplaces to be more diverse remains slow. want to read more about this? see full blog post - link in bio.

text:
i just lost 8lbs, i feel so much better, i really hope this is just the beginning. i've struggled with my weight my whole life; while refusing to be what people in the creative industries/men wanted me to be...i am not an object, i am a person! so the more i know i'm loved and loveable, i feel liberated to not have to hide myself. i know the man i love; loves me as i am, so i feel safe to climb out from underneath something that hid me. nobody wants to be loved just for their body. my technique is not a great life technique, i must admit, but i learned very quickly that people judge you upon the way you look, not upon your heart, not upon your character, i wanted to be loved for me in all my fullness. there is a lot of fullness to love. i'm not known for my figure, i'm known for my character and the way i make people feel. so i suppose i've felt safe enough to lose a little weight and get(as you can imagine) more counselling. i'm never going to be small, i'm not really built like that, but it's nice to feel good in my own skin without making it about receiving love and being an object. i am a woman not a fantasy. sorry for the over share but we all have unconscious emotions that drive our behaviour and i thought i'd be honest about some of mine!

#imnotanobjectimawoman #metoo  #weightlossjourney #dieting #loseweight #irememberwhoiam #imawomannotafantasy
