text:
lübecker lichter: holstentor. (2/3, dezember 2018)
.
letzte woche bin ich mit @dorfworker durch lübeck gezogen. das ergebnis dieses launigen fotowalks zeige ich in der aktuellen serie. nebenbei bemerkt: bei diesem spot haben wir zwei nette instagrammer kennengelernt: @jorioskari
und @amazing_shots18 - schaut auch mal bei deren galerien vorbei 😊
.
das weithin bekannte holstentor ist eigentlich gar nicht das holstentor - es stand in einer reihe mit drei anderen baugleichen toren und diente der stadtverteidigung. was mit den anderen passiert ist? das erzähl ich weiter unten. fangen wir vorne an.
.
im 15. jahrhundert machte der wohlstand lübecks stärkere verteidigungsanlagen nötig. es existierte bereits ein inneres holstentor, das aus dem 13. jahrhundert stammt und dem technischen fortschritt (bspw. kanonen) nicht mehr gewachsen war. deshalb brauchte die stadt ein neues und zwar das mittlere holstentor. es wurde 1478 fertiggestellt. hierbei handelt es sich um das heute noch bekannte.
.
etwa einhundert jahre später wurde das äußere holstentor im jahre 1585 vollendet. stünde es heute noch, würde es die sicht auf das mittlere holstentor verstellen.
.
1621 wurde das vierte holstentor errichtet, aber schon 1808 wieder zerstört. 1828 wurde das mittelalterliche innere holstentor abgerissen, 1853 das ältere äußere holstentor.
.
das schicksal stand auch dem mittleren holstentor bevor. der grund für die zerstörung der historischen stadttore war, dass sie angesichts der industrialisierung nur noch als hindernis im stadtbau galten. der preußische könig friedrich wilhelm iv. entsandte den königlichen konservator persönlich, um das alten tor vor diesem schicksal zu retten.
.
interesse an mehr geschichte und natur? @shores_in_flames folgen 😊
.

text: one of the best female boxers and boxers in general that you maybe never got the chance see, the startlingly impressive and unfortunately now retired @kalieshawest. her long hard fought battles in the ring and out are well documented as she strived to set a good example for the next generation by pushing for the exposure of female boxers whose talent was never lacking unlike the promotion. if things were different the public at large would’ve been in for a treat but luckily there is vid on her so pull it up for some real eye candy boxing fans. kaliesha i personally would like to say thank you for being you and continued success in all your endeavors. boxing is slowly changing and i would like to think that it’s because of people like you. #squad #realrecognizesreal #heresyourflowers #smelltheroses #boxers #boxer #boxing #boxeo #sweetscience #metoo #metoomovement #equality #equalrights #fairness

text: we’re still in need of gift cards! giving gift cards allows parents to purchase presents children need or want around the holidays but also gives them support year-around for living essentials. we prefer gift cards from retailers such as meijer, kroger, target and wal-mart.  in addition to these retailers, the center also welcomes visa/mastercard gift cards. for more information, contact 502-581-7207, or laura brock at laura.brock@cwfempower.org. drop off locations with link in bio.

text:
año nuevo 2012 me reuni con mi grupo de amigos de colegio, un grupo de mas de 10 personas donde yo soy la unica mujer. personalmente ellos siempre me dieron la confianza para sentirme segura entre ellos y asi mismo yo nunca les di razones para desconfiar de mi. salimos y como cualquiera en año nuevo bebimos hasta el amanecer. 10 hombres y una mujer bebiendo hasta el amanecer. me diverti? si!. bebi? si!. algunos terminaron durmiendo? si!. me violaron? no!.
es aqui donde parte la humanidad y educacion de cada uno, de lo que aprende uno afuera de su casa porque aunque tu sepas lo que es el abuso y lo que puedes hacer como hombre y en grupo a una mujer, no lo haces.
yo no tuve suerte, ellos se educaron y nunca intentaron hacerme algo malo, por el contrario, siempre fueron como mis hermanos mayores tratandome de la mejor manera porque yo era la unica mujer del grupo. aun con los juegos bruscos que teniamos, siempre hubo respeto. yo siempre voy a estar agradecida por el cariño que siempre nos hemos tenido aun con lo poco que hablamos actualmente, siempre los tengo en mi corazon y pensamientos.
no podemos excusar a un violador(o grupo de violadores) solo porque "es joven, no sabe lo que hace". y mucho menos, podemos culpar a la victima cuando ella fue la que fue abusada hasta el punto de la convulsion y casi muerte. dejemos de culpar a las victimas por salir solas, por como se visten, por tomar o no tomar. todos somos libres de hacer cualquiera de esas cosas. tratemos a los culpables por lo que son. violadores. y sobre todo, eduquemonos en el area de consentimiento. si ella dice que no. es no. y si esta tan intoxicada como para no saber lo que esta diciendo. es no. no nos convirtamos en complices de estos crimenes.
#niunamas #victimblaming #contraelabusosexual #hablalo #metoo #niunamenos #noestuculpa #tuluchaesmilucha #yotecreo  #santacruzbolivia #violacion #violenciasexual #lanuevamanada #abusosexual  #nonoscallamosmas #noesno

text:
do you have a hard time just being? ✨⁣
⁣
are your thoughts always focused on the future, the goals, the dreams, or even worrying about what’s to come? ⁣
⁣
i totally get it, i was that person... i still battle that person. i know what it’s like to constantly be pushing, pulling, striving,  charging, grasping for the future, the goals, the dreams and the accomplishments. ⁣
⁣
i also know how effing exhausting it is. i thought that it was the way successful people lived. how they became successful. ⁣
⁣
but as i started to study the successful people i looked up to there was a common theme. they all spoke of knowing when to slow down. they spoke of being present. they spoke of mindfulness. they spoke of stillness. they spoke of clarity. even if they weren’t fully present while gaining all of their success, they all spoke of how they would have focused more on that if they could go back. that’s how i feel now. ⁣
⁣
i wanted that. i needed that. ⁣
so that’s the journey i’ve been embarking on. for over a year, peeling back layers of the built up stress, worry, fear, anger...and discovering me. what’s crazy is i feel that i’m just getting started. i’m opening up channels of my being i didn’t even know existed. i’m feeling things i didn’t know were possible. and i’m being in ways i always dreamt of. slowly but surely. ⁣
⁣
am i still working? hell yes. just smarter.⁣
am i still setting goals? duh, but with more intention for the now. ⁣
⁣
i want you to know that if your goals are all you focus on, instead of the present moment and you create this pattern. then no matter what you achieve in the future, the future will always look better. you will never be satisfied no matter how successful you become. and i promise that’s no way to live. ⁣
⁣
i coach on this with my clients but one tip on focusing more on the present and living in the now, is to focus on gratitude in every moment. when you are grateful for the now, no matter how big or small, it keeps you in the present moment and keeps your spirit out of conflict. carrying around a gratitude journal or a note in your phone for when you need to get yourself in check is a good idea. ⁣
⁣
continued in comments

text:
delighted to participate in kochi-muzuris biennial 2018, and to put sound to these works. kudos #anitadube on your amazing vision and curation, i can’t wait to see! a clip from my animation adventures of the white beryl, 2018. many thanks to @nightfeelingss 👏🏾👏🏾sound design, with music by @browniebonbon77 and @aroojaftabmusic *
i want to acknowledge the current context of #metooindia unfolding in the art world, and overlapping with this year’s biennial — especially in light of survivors coming out and sharing their stories on social media, which has at times been negatively received. regardless of one’s issues with callout culture and tone (which i too have at times), that irritation cannot be used to justify an outright dismissal of people sharing their experiences of harassment, assault, and abuse of power. none of these stories surprise me. some i have heard before and know to be true. in a space as hierarchical and unforgiving as the art world, it could not be more important to have safe spaces for survivors to share their experiences. anonymously or not, it takes great courage, and survivors deserve justice. #believesurvivors  #kmb2018 #scorpiongesture #notsurprised  #feminismforever #timesarechangingwhetheryoulikeitornot #galleryespace #studionyc #rubinmuseum #kochibiennial #timesup #amplificationtheory #metoo

.

.

.
💫 queda mucho camino, pero tenemos que andarlo sin miedo
.

text:
as we countdown the final weeks of #2018, @newshour has a look back on the year in #photos. swipe to see the second set of shots that shaped the past 12 months. check back each week for more.

1️⃣britain's #princeharry gestures next to his wife #meghan as they ride a horse-drawn carriage after their wedding ceremony. #royalwedding

2️⃣naomi osaka of japan cries as @serenawilliams of the usa comforts her after the crowd booed during the trophy ceremony at the 2018 #usopen. osaka defeated williams in the final round of the competition.

3️⃣president donald #trump shakes hands with #northkorea’s kim jong un at the capella hotel on sentosa island in singapore

4️⃣saleh hassan al-faqeh holds the hand of his four-month-old daughter, hajar, who died at the malnutrition ward of al-sabeen hospital in #yemen

5️⃣victims and others look on as rachael denhollander speaks at the sentencing hearing for #larrynassar, a former team usa #gymnastics doctor who pleaded guilty in november 2017 to sexual assault charges

6️⃣ film producer #harveyweinstein arrives at manhattan criminal court in new york. weinstein was one of the first men accused of sexual misconduct in the #metoo movement.

7️⃣ two #immigrant families separated at the border relax after being reunited in el paso, texas.

8️⃣flowers and other items have been left as memorials outside the #treeoflife after a mass shooting at the synagogue that killed 11

9️⃣icebergs float in a fjord in greenland. according to the 2018 arctic report card, as global temperatures rise, the greenland ice sheet is slowly melting. #globalwarming #climatechange

1️⃣0️⃣#christineblaseyford appears before the senate judiciary committee to testify against #scotus nominee brett #kavanaugh. blasey ford accused kavanaugh of sexually assaulting her in high school.

photos: getty images, reuters pictures

text:
muitas mulheres são representadas na história como pecadoras e traidoras (eva e maria madalena), ou como santas (virgem maria). na idade média, o corpo da mulher (quando estava grávida) era visto como morada de deus, ou do diabo, quando diziam que elas corrompiam os homens, com sua sensualidade. na transição para o capitalismo, houve a caça às bruxas, o maior extermínio massivo de mulheres, motivado pelo ódio às mulheres livres, poderosas e donas de si.

a sexualidade feminina era vista como uma força a ser controlada e reprimida, pois só os desejos sexuais dos homens importavam. que natureza masculina é essa que tanto gosta de assediar, estrupar e matar? que sociedade é essa que tanto odeia mulheres livres e empoderadas?

nossas antepassadas sofreram por séculos essa opressão, porque eram domesticadas e não tinham voz. se uma mulher ousasse amar e se casar com alguém que não fosse escolhido pela família, e se atravesse a estudar e trabalhar, poderia ser agredida ou morta, sem ninguém questionar.

joão dos infernos simboliza a força do patriarcado, homens poderosos que abusam da vulnerabilidade de pessoas, que as manipulam para satisfazer seus desejos.

quando um homem “poderoso”, “ líder espiritualista”, é o agressor, vemos que é mais complicado o processo da denúncia. o risco de uma mulher ser ameaçada de morte triplica.

é preciso ter coragem. é preciso que uma mulher levante a outra. não podemos mais aceitar a violência de gênero normalizada em nossa sociedade.

espero que, um dia, não tenham medo de denunciar seus agressores, que não se importem com que a sociedade irá dizer, que estejam protegidas pelo estado e por pessoas queridas, que não sejam questionadas e tenham suas vidas viradas do avesso - para confirmar se são “santas” ou “putas”. minha solidariedade às mulheres que superaram o medo e que tiveram coragem de denunciar.

marias de deus, uni-vos!

frase da imagem @carolmachadoana

contact governor haslam at (615) 741-2001 -  black lives matter nashville, as well as activists nationwide, are calling on us to put pressure on tennessee’s outgoing governor to grant clemency to sex trafficking victim, cyntoia brown.

cyntoia brown was being abused emotionally and physically by a pimp who often held her at gunpoint.

in 2004 16 year old cyntoia brown was forced to have sex with a 43 year old man and fearing for her life she shot him with one of his many guns. for this, cyntoia brown was given life in prison for first-degree murder.

according to the root, "she was granted a clemency hearing earlier this year but her petition was eventually denied by the tennessee board of probation and parole. although the u.s. supreme court has ruled that life sentences without the possibility of parole for juveniles are unconstitutional, the tennessee supreme court later said that brown would have to serve at least 51 years of her sentence before she is granted parole." we must pressure tennessee governor bill haslam to grant her clemency before he leaves office in january!

black lives matter nashville wrote in a statement, "a system that disproportionately and intimately harms people of color, women, and other marginalized peoples is a matter of human rights. a system that allows the state of tennessee to have a unique sentencing of 51 years is a matter of human rights.” contact governor haslam at (615) 741-2001 to demand #clemency4cyntoiabrown. 
the group has issued a set of three phone scripts, available here 👉https://bit.ly/2srkr8a 👈  please act now!

#blacklivesmatter #freecyntoiabrown #freecyntoia
#metoo
#timesup

text:
i'm mad to be told: be careful, try to go with one of your friends, tell your father to go look for you with the car, keep talking to me on the phone in case someone bothers you ... i'm haract. in this life i should not be brave, nor live with fear, i should have the freedom to go as i please at the time i want and with whom i want.

because a precious hello is not a praise, it is a sign of danger, because your desire to seek pleasure is not mine, i want to get to my house alive and without having to run because i feel watched.

what's the difference if i wear a skirt or jeans? what difference does it make if i'm blond or brown? ... what's the matter, i'm still a person and your shitty compliments are nothing but shit, so if you think that by saying:, and that ass that does not pass hungry or dame to you mobile guapa you think you're doing me a favor, go away, seriously, you do not do anybody any good, you just get me to be afraid of you.

i am not a toy, i do not need your protection or your help, that being a man does not mean that you are better. being a man does not make you braver even a little bit.

when they tell you to be a man when you are afraid, send them for a walk, because i am a woman and i am more brave than any man in this world, i leave his street and despite having fear, i continue to live.

my body is only mine, or i choose if i want to teach it and i choose who. you are nobody to judge me.

if i want to go to 1am in a miniskirt, i'm not asking you to scream at me, if i'm a little drunk i'm not giving you the opportunity to abuse me, if i'm covered i'm not telling you to tell me i'm boring. .. just leave me alone.

and what is love? love is beautiful, and beautiful does not mean: darling, hold on a little, or, love, who are you going out with? uyuyuy give me your phone that i see you very happy talking to your "friends". love is not violent, love does not leave scratches on your skin, love does not eat you inside ... love does not force you to go further, love does not scream or hit you, does not control you or you obliges, love makes you fly, what a pity that some make that metaphor a reality. (continued in the comments)

text:
“¿cómo te puede dar miedo volver sola a casa?” algunos amigos míos nunca lo entenderán, pero por desgracia vosotras seguro que sí: ese ir corriendo hacia el portal, llevar las llaves ya cogidas dentro del bolso como un puño americano, hacer como que hablas por teléfono, acelerar el paso con la vista atrás, ponerte nerviosa cuando escuchas pasos detrás ... cuando oí la noticia se me encogió el corazón como con cada uno de estos terribles casos, pero esta vez sentí algo especial: profesora, de mi edad, habiendo estudiado bellas artes en valencia... teníamos muchas cosas en común, me hizo pensar que podría haber sido yo; y la verdad es que pudo haber sido cualquiera, una chica normal que sale a hacer deporte.

laura no lo pudo haber expresado mejor y creo que esto solo se puede combatir desde la educación y concienciación social. 
lucharemos por tí 
#lauraluelmo y por todas las que se fueron 💜.
__________________________

text:
what if acts of service went viral instead of booty pics? 🔺️fyi, i know this pic doesn't work for the ig algorithm.🔻 booty pic: 1 million shares, viral💃💃💃 act of service: 7 likes, crickets 🦗🦗🦗🦗 conclusion: wtf!?!?!?🤷‍♂️🤔🤔 why does a pic of some girl or guy's ass or abs produce countless positive replies and shares. however pics of "acts of service" are scrutinized and usually disregarded. people ask:

why are they showing the pic & trying to get praise?
are they trying to get applause or be seen as a good person?

well what if they were? so what?!?!? is a selfish person giving someone in need money, better than a selfish person taking a pic for personal gain? --- i walked out of 7-11 and gave a homeless man 7 dollars because i wanted him to feel lucky! that was it. i had the money...i gave it!

if you feel so inclined, feel free to challenge my intentions around the act. why did i do it? what is my intention of doing it and taking a picture? what is sanyika looking to achieve?

i want you to challenge the reason i gave it,  when i gave it, and what my purpose was in giving.

then after you're done... i want it to be so scrutinized that it encourages other people to do the exact same thing. i dont need this to go viral, but i want the idea to resonate with you so powerfully that you do it as well. 
there are people in need...not just the homeless!!! -your elderly neighbor (ask to wash their car)
-your kids friend (might need a place to stay for a few weeks because of turmoil at home)

text:
i wanted to be a flight attendant 👩‍✈️ growing up, it was the only career/job i thought would help me escape my family, my childhood. i wanted to forget the things i saw, the things that happened at the hands of my family. the emotional, physical and verbal abuse. 
i remember quietly filling out the paperwork to be a flight attendant after my at the time boyfriend broke my heart in a way that can never be forgotten, who sleeps with your own cousin? only an asshole could!

i thought that at that time that was the hardest life would be but the truth is that it only got worse. i found out that life got harder, more complicated, that people always hurt you, trust was easily broken. 
i was sexually assaulted at 17 years old by a male friend and my life forever would be changed, i got pregnant and never made it to be a flight attendant. instead i became a mom. 
my life has been one hell after the other so i decided to write recently, i want to pour my pain, anger and every other emotion i feel on paper for the world to read but i’m scared, i’m anxious that i will fail. 
what if i suck? what if no one likes what i write? do i want to deal with another disappointment? 
any advice?

text: miriam hopkins died of a heart attack on october 9, 1972 in new york city; she had been in town for a rare screening of the story of temple drake (1933) at moma. she was born ellen miriam hopkins on october 18, 1902 in savannah, georgia. she moved with her mother to syracuse, new york after her parents separated. she first appeared on broadway as a performer in the music box revue of 1921. she was then cast in several broadway productions through the 1920s including an american tragedy, the garden of eden, & excess baggage which were all later adapted into motion pictures without her. paramount pictures signed her to a contract in 1930 while she continued to act on broadway. her 1st feature length talkie was fast and loose (1930); she had previously appeared in a talkie short, the home girl (1928). she was the favorite actress of several of paramount's finest directors like ernst lubitsch & rouben mamoulian. she left paramount in 1934 & appeared in screwball comedies and romantic dramas for rko & samuel goldwyn for the rest of the 1930s. she signed a contract with warner brothers in 1939 & made a couple of films with her on/off-screen nemesis bette davis--the old maid (1939) & old acquaintance (1943). she returned to broadway when film offers declined in the 1940s, but she returned for 2 excellent william wyler films: the heiress (1949) & the children's hour (1961). throughout the 1950s and 1960s, she also appeared in such television shows as route 66, the outer limits, & lux video theatre. she was nominated once for an academy award for best actress: becky sharp (1935). she was an intelligent, well read person in private life & was a lifelong supporter of the democratic party (although she had brief conservative periods). she married 4 times, most famously to director anatole litvak; she also adopted her son michael in 1932 while she was a singleton. this portrait of fredric march, gary cooper, & her was for ernst lubitsch's adaptation of noël coward's design for living (1933). #miriamhopkins #travisbanton #fredricmarch #garycooper #ernstlubitsch  #noëlcoward #designforliving #paramountpictures #academyawardnominee #precode #democrat #gownsbytravisbanton

she had previously appeared in a talkie short, the home girl (1928). she was the favorite actress of several of paramount's finest directors like ernst lubitsch & rouben mamoulian. she left paramount in 1934 & appeared in screwball comedies and romantic dramas for rko & samuel goldwyn for the rest of the 1930s. she signed a contract with warner brothers in 1939 & made a couple of films with her on/off-screen nemesis bette davis--the old maid (1939) & old acquaintance (1943). she returned to broadway when film offers declined in the 1940s, but she returned for 2 excellent william wyler films: the heiress (1949) & the children's hour (1961). throughout the 1950s and 1960s, she also appeared in such television shows as route 66, the outer limits, & lux video theatre. she was nominated once for an academy award for best actress: becky sharp (1935). she was an intelligent, well read person in private life & was a lifelong supporter of the democratic party (although she had brief conservative periods). she married 4 times, most famously to director anatole litvak; text:
here's what i know:  there is a flip side to everything. 
a counter thought, feeling and belief for every thought, feeling and belief we have. 
and i know that while the holiday season, wrapping up the end of the year and starting a new year is filled with peace, joy and excitement for many, it can be a time of sadness, hopelessness and grief for others.
.

we have to talk about it.
.

according to mentalhealth.net up to 15% of the adult population and up to 25% of adolescents will experience depression at some point.
.

depression is real.  and it may not look like it's portrayed in the movies.  it may look like everything is perfectly okay on the outside and someone can still be in deep despair and turmoil on the inside.
.

the good thing is that depression is treatable. 
be it through talk therapy, medication, nutrition, exercise, meditation, aromatherapy or many other modalities. 
yet for any of these to work, we need to be able to let someone know how we're really feeling. 
that can be a scary first step, but it's necessary.
.

one of the quickest ways to begin to shift from depression is to focus on what you're grateful for. 
thoughts become feelings which become beliefs and we have the power to intercept our depressed thoughts and replace them with thoughts of gratitude. it's not the whole solution, but it can definitely be a part of your support plan.
.

brain science confirms an attitude of grattitude can actually change our mood.  so give it a try.  make a habit of listing what you're gratefiul for. not just the big stuff, but the itty bitty stuff too.
.

and please get help. understand that there is no shame in feeling your feelings, even depression. 
let someone know.
whether you reach out to a friend, family member, someone at your place of worship, a life coach, therapist, counselor, teacher, doctor, helpline or other....let help in.
.

thankfully, you don't have to suffer with depression alone.
.

will you reach out today?  either to get support or give support or just to check in and hold space for someone?
let's talk about it.
.
💜
.
*if you are feeling depressed and/or suicidal call 91(usa) or google search a hotline number in your area.

text:
do you know your “little girl” within?
.
close your eyes and for a few seconds try to get a sense of her...how old is she? how tall is she? see her little face...does she seem sad, happy, playful or curious? is she energized? is she tired or lethargic?
.
you can ask her what she needs most from you, right now... listen to what she has to tell you...stay there for a few seconds...
.
#internalfamilysystems 
internal family systems aka ifs therapy is a powerful tool for healing trauma. ifs is based on “multiplicity of the mind”.... it incorporates the concept of #innerchild as a “part” within us. parts come forward when needed/necessary! all parts within us are welcome! .
art by #brucepennington via @retro_scifiart .
.
.
.
.

text:
le pido al 2019 que la sociedad sea consciente de que el heteropatriarcado existe. nos humillan, nos acosan, nos violan, nos maltratan, nos matan... y encima no nos creen. “¿por qué hay tantas mujeres que no denuncian?”, es una pregunta que muchos se hacen. por miedo a la sociedad, a la justicia y a la propia muerte a manos de la violencia machista.

podéis seguir mirando a otro lado, creyendo que se trata de casos aislados, pensando que “ella se lo buscó” o “algo habría hecho”. lo que sé es que las feministas (y los aliados) estamos cada vez más unidas y vamos a por todas. ya que no nos van a ayudar a sobrevivir, nos apoyaremos entre nosotras. y sí, ya lo estamos haciendo: cada vez más coordinadas, más valientes, más preparadas y con una sororidad que crea incluso miedo a los “machirulos” que siempre han intentado que las mujeres peleemos entre nosotras. vuestro momento se ha acabado, estamos juntas, estamos unidas. es cuestión de vida o muerte, porque sí, nos están matando... y tú puedes ser la próxima víctima. #niunamás #niunamenos

text_retweet:
did you know? 
eka pāda rājakapotasana- (pigeon pose) rājakapota meaning king of pigeons. 
stretches the quadriceps, hip flexors, abdomen, thorax, ankles, groin, psoas (large muscles that starts at the sides of your lumbar& runs down to your groin). this asana has many variations, for beginners-you can start in a chair! yes a chair!!! of course, this one depicted in the picture is appropriate for intermediate, and of course advanced, taking this asana straight into king pigeon, for the ultimate hip opener! 
our hips carry all kinds of baggage, since our very first hurt, loss, broken heart, it all adds up and as we continue to pile shit into them, we begin creating arthritis, lower back pain-shooting down the mega to the feet, causing even more troubles, like hip replacements, that is why it is essential to open them up and release all the stagnation in them! “i have injuries and i am not flexible!” “can i still do pigeon pose if you’ve already had a hip
replacement?” yes, yes and yes!! there is not one person i know, who has not moved in a long time who is flexible lol, time heals all things and that includes your body, mind and eventually soul! 
remember, as long as your doctor is on board, & believe me doctors now see how yoga benefits the body! start with the chair & work your way up! if you now sure look for my youtube video!! blessings to all 🥰🙌🕉💟 @@@@@@@

text:
in the heart of holiday giving, we are thrilled to announce our @onthemendretreat scholarship, for a value of 40% off.
•
can you envision yourself waking up in a cozy and serene lodge high up in the california mountains, or taking in the sunrise amongst the joshua tree desert? how about unplugging, moving inward, flowing & stretching, breaking bread and forming community over fireside chats and nourishing meals? how about finding peace, forgiveness, acceptance and freeing yourself from past heartache? sounds like a dream right? if you can envision it, we want to support you in making that dream a reality.
•
we are now accepting submissions through 1.4.19. to enter:
👉🏻 visit the “california healing retreat” link in my bio
👉🏻 join seek retreat
👉🏻 press “request booking” to apply for the retreat (no payment needed)
👉🏻 submit your response in the text box, explaining why this healing retreat is so important to you!
•• we will announce the winner on 1.5.19. we can’t wait to get to know you all more, and walk alongside you in this journey!
•
**those who have already signed up or applied for the retreat are not eligible to apply for this scholarship.
•
•
•
•

text:
in the heart of holiday giving, we are thrilled to announce our @onthemendretreat scholarship, for a value of 40% off.
•
can you envision yourself waking up in a cozy and serene lodge high up in the california mountains, or taking in the sunrise amongst the joshua tree desert? how about unplugging, moving inward, flowing & stretching, breaking bread and forming community over fireside chats and nourishing meals? how about finding peace, forgiveness, acceptance and freeing yourself from past heartache? sounds like a dream right? if you can envision it, we want to support you in making that dream a reality.
•
we are now accepting submissions through 1.4.19. to enter:
👉🏻 visit the “on the mend idyllwild” link in our bio
👉🏻 join seek retreat
👉🏻 press “request booking” to apply for the retreat (no payment needed)
👉🏻 submit your response in the text box, explaining why this healing retreat is so important to you!
•• we will announce the winner on 1.5.19. we can’t wait to get to know you all more, and walk alongside you in this journey!
•
**those who have already signed up or applied for the retreat are not eligible to apply for this scholarship.
•
•
•
•

text:
how to cultivate a tribe around your brand 💫
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
to cultivate a tribe around your brand that embodies who you are and what you stand for, you can do the following things:
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
1. start your own fb community - this is a great way to start getting awareness around your brand and offer and really speak directly to your ideal clients and followers (like i am doing for you all right now)
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
2. start a blog - most of you in here are bloggers or beginning your own blog. congrats on those who are beginning the journey! a blog is a great way to get out there and start creating a community around your brand. i suggest starting with a niche on your blog (i.e. fitness, fashion, entrepreneurship, business, travel, food etc.). that way you can become known for that specific thing and then expand on that solid foundation.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
3. do small things for your followers and clients - sometimes it’s the little things that make the biggest impact online. the brands that i remember are the ones that give a special, personalized note in their packages. i do this by doing small giveaways in my ig stories (if you haven’t looked there, be sure you do)! i will also be doing this for my p2p students :)
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
4. give value after value - this one never gets old. think about how you can give value to your followers and clients. will this leave them better than when they first read the post? if the answer is yes, you are one step closer to looking at your potential client!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
5. create a movement - use a specific hashtag to create a movement around your brand that is specific to your brand. if you are a blogger this could look like #abmlifeisbeautiful or #metoo for example, are two hashtags that literally created a movement.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
there are many more tidbits on how to create that true #vibetribe, but the most important is be so authentically you that no one can touch you and your vibe tribe. no one can f*ck with your vibration 💯

text:
one of the most important lessons i teach in this book is “no matter what you’ve been through you still deserve to be loved the way you want to be loved.”⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
::⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
this is such a hard concept a lot of times for black women because we believe our value is wrapped up in how much we sacrifice and do for others. we get manipulated into thinking that because we’ve had a life and experiences that we no longer get to ask for and have what we want.::⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
this is a bold face lie, a trick of the devil and some bullshit. your value is unconditional and never changes no matter what and anyone trying to get you to believe otherwise needs to go and jump off a cliff.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
::⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
click the link in my bio to get a copy and learn more. #fuckthatcape #healblackwomen  #healinggoals

text:
i spent the flights to/from barcelona reading a powerful forthcoming book about pattabhi jois and sexual assault in the yoga world. oof. it shook me. we yoga teachers will be unpacking this stuff for years to come. 😳
.
if you want to learn more (‘cause it ain’t going away, folks), start here with karen rain’s @medium article from earlier this fall. karen is not on instagram, but she and i have been in touch since my earlier post recommending her podcast with @jbrownyoga, and i made sure to share your supportive comments and loving solidarity with her.
.
at a time when yoga history is in major revisionist mode, primary sources are the place to turn. karen’s voice is one of many we should be listening to and amplifying right now. link to her full article in my bio.
.
#yoga #ashtanga #vinyasa #power #hotyoga #yogi #poweryoga #pattabhijois #sexualassault #guru #metoo #feminist #history #yogateacher #yogagirl #yogapose #yogaeverywhere #yogachallenge #traumasensitiveyoga #practice #bodies #trauma #embodiment #healing #practiceandalliscoming #selfcare #yogaeverydamnday #om #namaste
